7.16	Abbas_(photographer)	Abbas (photographer)	Abbas Attar' (Persian: â€Ž) (born 1944) is an Iranian photographer known for his photojournalism in Biafra, Vietnam and South Africa in the 1970s, and for his extensive essays on religions in later years. He was a member of Sipa from 1971 to 1973, a member of Gamma (agency) from 1974 to 1980, and joined Magnum Photos in 1981.	
